Objective:
	It is a spring Batch Account Enquiry Processing Module. It reads the pending records from the database, calls the EIS Account Enquiry API, decrypts the response, validates the response fields, updates the database based on different conditions, and supports retry/error handling. Based on the validation results, the module updates the transaction status and records appropriate error information in the database.

Architecture:
	The module follows the spring batch architecture, which consists of the following components:
•	Reader – Reads the pending account enquiry records from the database.
•	Processor – Prepares the request and invokes the EIS Account Enquiry API.
•	Writer – Validates the response and updates the database.
•	Job Configuration – controls the execution flow of the batch job.
•	Partitioning – Enables parallel processing of records to improve performance.


